sbol:Collection.dcterms:title: iGEM Parts Registry
sbol:Collection.dcterms:description: The iGEM Registry is a growing collection of genetic parts that can be mixed and matched to build synthetic biology devices and systems. As part of the synthetic biology community's efforts to make biology easier to engineer, it provides a source of genetic parts to iGEM teams and academic labs.

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_K1471011
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: The initiation of protein biosynthesis is a major determinant of the efficiency of gene expression at the translational level. It is known that the nucleotide sequences around the AUG translation initiation codon act as an important signal to trigger the initiation of the translation event. (Kozak, 1987)
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Juan Noe Hernandez Salazar
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes: We had to discuss what was the best option to enhance the expression efficiency of our proteins of interest to bio-remediate heavy metals, as mercury.
